<html>
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
	<head>
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
		<title>Upgrade of subscription contact system</title>
		<!-- <from>%22Adrian Raper, Clarity%22 %3Cadrian.raper@clarityenglish.com%3E</from> -->
		<!-- <bcc>adrian.raper@clarityenglish.com</bcc> -->
</head>
<div style="width:600px; margin:0 auto; padding:0;">
	<img src="http://www.clarityenglish.com/images/email/email_banner.jpg" alt="Clarity English - Support information" style="border:0; margin:0; text-align:center"/>
    <div style="width:500px; margin:a auto; padding:10px 50px 20px 50px;">
		<p style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; margin:0 0 10px 0; padding:0; color:#000000;">Dear Colleague</p>
		<p style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#000000; margin:0 0 10px 0; padding:0;">Your account: <strong>{$account->name}</strong></p>
		<p style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#000000; margin:0 0 10px 0; padding:0;">This email is to let you know about a change we are making to how we send emails to you regarding your Clarity English subscription. There are four upgrades to the current system:</p>
		<p style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#000000; margin:0 0 10px 0; padding:0;">1) Firstly we have added an email control section to your Results Manager pages. Here you can set which of your colleagues gets what sort of email. For example, you might want support messages to go to teachers and service messages to go to technicians. You can add extra email addresses and a grid lets you select who gets what. As an administrator you will always get service messages (notification of upgrades etc) and usage statistics.</p>
		<p style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#000000; margin:0 0 10px 0; padding:0;">2) The monthly usage statistics email will not arrive on the 1st of each month, but on the same day as your licence started. For instance, if your subscription started on the 15th of the month, usage statistics will always arrive on the 15th of each month.</p>
		<p style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#000000; margin:0 0 10px 0; padding:0;">3) The reminders letting you know when your subscription will need renewing are changing. Note that if your renewal is coming up in the next month - you may get an email that appears to be part of a series. This will only happen once as part of the changeover. Each email now contains all the information you need to see the renewal details.</p>
		<p style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#000000; margin:0 0 10px 0; padding:0;">4) If you have just started a subscription, we will send some support emails to help you get the most out of your account.</p>
		<p style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#000000; margin:0 0 10px 0; padding:0;">I hope that the changes give you more control, and improve our communication with you. Please do let me know if you have any questions or comments about this. </p>
	{include file='file:includes/TechnicalDirector_Email_Signature.tpl'}
